They use a sophisticated echolocation technique to detect insects and obstacles on their flight itinerary.
Responsible for the protection of more than 270 historic buildings, 38 important gardens and 76,000 hectares of land in the country, the NTS takes bats very seriously.
It has ten trained experts, who regularly conduct surveys, perchoir inspections and sometimes rescues.
The organization also established Scotland's first and only reserve of bats at the Thrave site in Dumfries-et-Galloway, home to eight of Scotland's ten bat species.
